Directive_Context.Mission:
Turn the operator's raw idea into an approved root-level project spec via an iterative stack-based process.

First session of the SDD flow. Input — raw idea (or existing spec link / `specs/README.md` Portal for extension/pivot). Outputs:
- self-contained `specs/.spec.md` containing:
  - Vision & Primary Goal;
  - Project Type (`app[mobile/desktop/spa]` | `service-module-sdk` | `cli-utility`);
  - Approved Golden DX Example;
  - Frozen Requirements & Constraints;
  - Chosen High-Level Architecture (selected variant + brief notes on rejected ones);
  - Decision Log with explicit operator rationale;
  - Handoff contract for `module-decomposition`.
- own row + `## Vision` section in `specs/README.md` Specs Portal (created in greenfield, updated in extension/pivot).

Out of scope here: module decomposition, entity inventory, DbC contracts — those belong to `module-decomposition`.

**Glossary.** Phase 1 of SDD: discovery (1) → module-decomposition (2) → task-scaffolding (3) → task-execution (4) → audit (5). Infra-discovery is a parallel orthogonal track (see `infra-discovery` directive).

Belief_State.Axiom:
Architectural variants are forbidden until REQUIREMENTS_GATE closes. Required:
- Functional Requirements: what the system MUST do;
- Non-Functional Constraints: performance, security, compatibility, operational, observability — scaled by Project Type;
- Out-of-Scope: deliberately deferred from v1;
- Project-Wide Rules per `AX_PROJECT_RULES_DECLARATION`.

Design without frozen requirements collapses into rationalization around convenient assumptions.

Pivot Handoff lists explicit downstream artifacts that became stale. §7 is augmented with §7.1 Pivot Invalidation List per `PIVOT_INVALIDATION_LIST_FORMAT`:
- **Module specs requiring `refine-module`**;
- **Tasks requiring reopen** (TSK-NN);
- **Rules to revisit**.

Without this list, downstream cannot know what to revisit. Pivot without invalidation list → halt with explicit warning.
